(226, 1, '2021-07-11 17:55:22', '2021-07-11 17:55:22', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The move points to Mr Biden\'s desire for tougher scrutiny of Big Tech, which the administration has accused of \"undermining competition\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Capitalism without competition isn\'t capitalism. It\'s exploitation,\" Mr Biden said at Friday\'s signing event.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The order includes 72 actions and recommendations involving ten agencies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It suggests that problems have arisen because of large tech firms collecting too much personal information, buying up potential competitors and competing unfairly with small businesses.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Several recommendations it sets out include:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Greater scrutiny of mergers in the tech sector</li><li>New rules to be set out by the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) on data collection</li><li>Barring unfair methods of competition on internet marketplaces.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Biden administration is also targeting a number of other sectors with the order.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It encourages other government agencies to take action to improve competition across healthcare, travel and agriculture.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once fully implemented, it would allow hearing aids to be sold over the counter, for example, as well as the ban of early exit fees from internet contracts. It also intends to make it easier for consumers to claim refunds from airlines.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Biden signs new order cracking down on Big Tech', 'President Joe Biden has signed an executive order aimed at cracking down on big tech firms and promoting competition.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '224-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-07-11 17:55:22', '2021-07-11 17:55:22', '', 224, 'http://localhost/WordPress/supershop/?p=226', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(227, 1, '2021-07-11 17:58:49', '2021-07-11 17:58:49', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":229,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/WordPress/supershop/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/119327569_punnet1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-229\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Whether their favourite players win or lose, crowds flocking to The Wimbledon Tennis Championships find pleasure, or consolation, in the food that\'s become an event staple - strawberries and cream.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Over 100,000 punnets are scoffed during Wimbledon fortnight with a staggering 7000 litres of cream. Now UK scientists have come up with a new variety of strawberry, which they hope could extend these hungry snackers\' enjoyment further through summer and well into autumn.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The new berry on the block is called the Malling Ace. And for the last six years, researchers at NIAB in East Malling, Kent - the UK\'s largest horticulture research and development centre - have been tinkering with strawberry varieties to come up with one they feel not only suits British palates, but makes growing and harvesting easier for the producers</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Why strawberry experts are hoping to serve up an Ace', 'Whether their favourite players win or lose, crowds flocking to The Wimbledon Tennis Championships find pleasure, or consolation, in the food that\'s become an event staple - strawberries and cream', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-strawberry-experts-are-hoping-to-serve-up-an-ace', '', '', '2021-07-11 17:58:49', '2021-07-11 17:58:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/WordPress/supershop/?p=227', 0, 'post', '', 0),
